need help to make a new resume for a job at a dentist's office im currently looking for a new job at a dentist or orthodontist office i want to go to school to become a dental hygentist so i think working at a dentist office would really help me at school i also want to have a good part time or full time job that offers benefits i havn't made a resume for about a year and don't really know how to make a proper one anymore any help would be appreciated thanks besides setting all margins to the most important criteria for setting up a professional resume besides relevant text is scanability here are some helpful tips place just below your identification header your hame address phone email address any conditional warning statement such as confidential resume do not contact current employer etc always fill in an objectives category just below the conditional warning statement and make sure that he objective will contribute to the profitability of your future employer select a mono type font such as helvetica arial courier or times roman do not select any cursive handwriting styles which cannot scanned keep font sizes within a range of to pts avoid styling text with a justified alignment keep it flushed left instead of using tabs to set up blocked text entries generate a table and use the column and row settings accordingly do not place an i d picture anywhere on the resume this is a major taboo due to discrimination issues do not place any graphic text saved as gifs onto the resume since it may be overlooked during the scanning phase list at the very end of the resume your interests which should include travel experiences language skills social interactions such as golf team sports tennis etc in conclusion the above helpful hints were designed to allow ease of scanning of your resume into pdf which can then be text captured for seach purposes by your potential employer if the original resume was created in word wordperfect or mac appleworks it can be saved as a pdf file which then can be saved as an email attachment otherwise you can simply use a scanner and scan a hard copy of the resume and then save as a pdf file failure to conform the resume to appropriate fonts and styles as outlined above will result in rejection of the resume simply due to the inability of the scanning device to properly index relevant resume entries good luck Killian documents Typeface Gmail HTML element Portable Document Format EIA-708 TrueType Unicode CPU cache OpenDocument Apple typography Computer virus PostScript Ebook WordPerfect ALGOL 68 Google Enterprise content management PNG Plame affair Opera (web browser) E-mail spam International Phonetic Alphabet Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus HTML British national identity card Insurance Python programming language Cascading Style Sheets IPod Virtual memory Palanca Awards Windows Vista Cyrillic alphabet Medical prescription Computer Atari 8-bit family System/36 ASCII art Stopping e-mail abuse Hangul Pretty Good Privacy System/34 Mach kernel Perl E-mail Emacs Windows XP Magnetic resonance imaging Compiler optimization Microsoft Screenshot Economic inequality Index (database) Macromedia Flash Arabic alphabet Apple Computer Social Security (United States) SCO-Linux controversies Hash table Digital photography Euro Objective-C Intelligent design movement Mac OS X Blog Forth programming language Downing Street memo Anonymous remailer Stuttering Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act HyperCard AmigaOS Dot matrix printer Phishing Geographic information system Dentistry Musical Instrument Digital Interface Unicode and HTML Tennis Volleyball File format Icon programming language United Kingdom corporation tax Intellectual property Optical character recognition Unemployment Baptism Philosophy of language Customer relationship management Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol Microeconomics 